What you need to know:  A confidential report on how to end banditry and cattle rustling in the North Rift region informed President William Ruto’s order for the deployment of Kenya Defence Forces’ soldiers to a joint security operation with the police, the Nation has learnt.The document dubbed Technical Report on National Shared Security Strategy for Enduring Peace and Security in the North Rift Region was handed to the President this month.The document will guide the next phase of “Operation Komesha Uhalifu North Rift”, which was launched in September last year following the killing of a local chief, two civilians and eight police officers by bandits in Turkana East.